英国近一半的年轻人喜欢低酒精或不含酒精的饮料https://www.nme.com/news/music/nearly-half-of-young-people-in-the-uk-prefer-low-or-non-酒精-drinks-3566145?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=近一半的英国年轻人更喜欢低酒精或不含酒精的饮料Will RichardsFri, 05 Jan 2024 11:57:26 +0000 Music NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3566145 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="酒精" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> YouGov 的一项新调查显示，39% 的 18 至 24 岁人群根本不喝酒</p><p>这篇文章<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nearly-half-of-young-people-in-the-uk-prefer-low-or-non-alcoholic-drinks-3566145">《近一半的英国年轻人喜欢低度或不含酒精的饮料》</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="酒精" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/alcohol-survey-gettty-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>一项新调查显示，近一半的英国年轻人更喜欢低酒精或不含酒精的饮料。</p><p> YouGov 和波特曼集团的<a href="https://www.portmangroup.org.uk/yougov-survey-shows-rise-in-popularity-of-low-and-no-alcohol-alternatives-with-young-adults-now-the-biggest-consumers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">调查</a>揭示了 Z 世代成员对酒精态度的变化，18 至 24 岁的人中 39% 根本不喝酒。</p><p> 44% 的“最清醒年龄组”认为自己偶尔或经常饮用 0% 酒精替代品——这一数字较 2022 年增加了 13%。</p><p> 23% 的受访者表示，选择低酒精或不含酒精的饮料会降低他们的总体酒精摄入量。</p><p>波特曼集团首席执行官马特·兰伯特 (Matt Lambert) 表示：“我们很高兴看到低酒精和无酒精替代品的受欢迎程度进一步上升，并进一步证明它们是帮助英国饮酒者，特别是年轻人饮酒的重要工具。负责任地。</p><p> “酒精替代品的供应从未如此丰富，我们热切地等待英国政府最近关于低酒精描述符的磋商结果，我们希望这将进一步促进英国低酒精和无酒精市场的增长。”</p><p>去年进行的一项调查还显示， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/gen-z-are-twice-as-likely-to-bunk-off-work-to-go-to-a-concert-than-millennials-3497838">43% 的 Z 世代愿意戒酒六个月，</a>以获得在他们最喜欢的音乐会上坐在前排的机会。 </p><figure id="attachment_2632481" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2632481" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-2632481" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pintbeer.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pintbeer.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pintbeer-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pintbeer-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pintbeer-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pintbeer-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pintbeer-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2632481" class="wp-caption-text"> （图片：盖蒂）</figcaption></figure><p>这些数据是在<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-nightlife-industry-share-anger-over-increased-alcohol-duty-and-drink-prices-3476297">英国夜生活行业对去年英国酒类税和饮料价格上涨表示愤怒之后</a>发布的。</p><p>去年8月，总理里希·苏纳克(Rishi Sunak)和财政大臣杰里米·亨特(Jeremy Hunt)提出了一项计划，将增税幅度提高到20%。</p><p>此举遭到了夜间产业协会的强烈谴责，该协会声称“今天计划增加的酒类税可能会对本已陷入困境的行业造成严重损害，而该行业在我们国家的经济和文化活力中发挥着至关重要的作用”。</p><p> 2023 年，苏格兰最大的现场音乐推广商 DF Concerts &amp; Events 表示， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/scotlands-biggest-live-music-promoter-warns-that-alcohol-sponsorship-ban-will-be-disastrous-for-industry-3398477">禁止酒精赞助现场活动的提议对现场行业来说将是“灾难性的”</a> 。</p><p>在<a href="https://consult.gov.scot/alcohol-policy/alcohol-advertising-and-promotion/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">苏格兰政府关于限制酒类广告提案的磋商</a>中， <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/trnsmt">TRSNMT</a>和格拉斯哥夏季会议（这两项 DF 活动）被列为非体育赛事广告和促销部分的示例。</p><p>这篇文章<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nearly-half-of-young-people-in-the-uk-prefer-low-or-non-alcoholic-drinks-3566145">《近一半的英国年轻人喜欢低度或不含酒精的饮料》</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
